      "writtenOn": "2018-10-12T13:50:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "... Another grievance I have is that glog.Fatal() doesn\u0027t actually create a panic.  It dumps the stacktrace and then does os.Exit(255).  Therefore, deferred funcs do not run, and it\u0027s impossible to recover or flush any non-sklog cloud loggers, close open files, etc etc.",
      "parentUuid": "9e5c52bd_3a6ad8a7",
      "revId": "3400f4cb8ad9dbe096a38801c0068822646551e3",
