      "writtenOn": "2018-10-12T15:40:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, that will be a huge change across all of our libraries no matter which one we pick.\n\nGiven we want concurrency I think that going back to the pre-context code would be good, but dropping the Done(\u0026err) in that iteration in favor\nstep.Failed(err).",
      "parentUuid": "88d895be_6d63334d",
      "revId": "3400f4cb8ad9dbe096a38801c0068822646551e3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f09a52b7_c6707b5d",
        "filename": "go/task_driver/examples/basic/basic.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 154,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-12T15:55:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why go back to pre-context?  We can still do concurrency with contexts, as long as they\u0027re passed around properly, and IMO it\u0027s much more natural for a context to be passed to every function call than passing a Step everywhere.  Plus, if we did add a context to sklog, we\u0027d be able to just pass the same context through.",
      "parentUuid": "97b31057_4c8df467",
      "revId": "3400f4cb8ad9dbe096a38801c0068822646551e3",
